SIMPLE: furring
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Furring
<hw>Fur"ring</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Carp.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The leveling of a surface, or the
preparing of an air space, by means of strips of board or of larger
pieces. See <er>Fur</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, 3.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The strips thus laid on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>Double planking of a
ship's side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A deposit from water, as on the inside of a boiler;
also, the operation of cleaning away this deposit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Furrow</ent>⟦br⟧
